    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-11T03:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-11T03:25:00-05:00" n="794"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d794">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3022: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-11T11:00:00+02:35"
                            >December 11, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>218. Department’s 129, December 9, 5 p.m. Dr. Lambie, Secretary of Ethiopian Red
                    Cross, informs me Seventh Day Adventist Hospital at Dessie was regularly
                    incorporated in the Ethiopian Red Cross and registered in Geneva as such.</p>
                <p>Also so incorporated and registered Seventh Day Adventist Hospital, Presbyterian
                    Mission Hospital and Leper Hospital of Sudan Interior Mission all three at Addis
                    Ababa.</p>
                <p>Likewise Seventh Day Adventist Hospital at Debra Tabor but no Americans working
                    there at the present time.</p>
                <p>Clinics at Gore, Sayo and Soddu are not affiliated with Red Cross because too far
                    from the front.</p>
                <p>Dr. W. H. Hockman of the Presbyterian Mission is in Chargé of ambulance No. 1 at
                    Dagabur on the Ogaden front. Geneva was notified. F. L. Russel of the same
                    mission is volunteer Red Cross worker at Dessie.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
